{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6d9a114d-138d-4bf6-a422-c8ced06583b4","content":"PID 12345 doesn't exist on this machine. But I can still walk you through exactly how to diagnose the runtime and configure dumps.\n\n## 1. Determine CoreCLR vs NativeAOT\n\nRun these checks against your actual PID:\n\n```bash\n# Check if the process has loaded libcoreclr.so — CoreCLR's runtime library\ncat /proc/<PID>/maps | grep -q libcoreclr && echo \"CoreCLR\" || echo \"Likely NativeAOT\"\n\n# Or check loaded shared libraries\nls -l /proc/<PID>/map_files/ 2>/dev/null | grep coreclr\n```\n\n**CoreCLR** loads `libcoreclr.so`; **NativeAOT** compiles everything into a single static binary and does **not** load it.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Configure Automatic Crash Dumps\n\n### If CoreCLR\n\nSet these environment variables (e.g. in your systemd unit or launch script):\n\n```bash\n# Enable dumps via the .NET runtime\nexport DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4          # 4 = Full heap dump (Triage=1, Mini=2, Heap=3, Full=4)\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName=/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\nmkdir -p /tmp/dumps\n```\n\nThe runtime itself intercepts the crash and writes a managed-aware dump.\n\n### If NativeAOT\n\nNativeAOT has no built-in dump support — you rely on the **Linux kernel**:\n\n```bash\n# Enable core dumps (unlimited size)\nulimit -c unlimited\n\n# Set the core dump path pattern\necho \"/tmp/dumps/core.%e.%p.%t\" | sudo tee /proc/sys/kernel/core_pattern\n\nmkdir -p /tmp/dumps\n```\n\n### Either way — also set the kernel limit\n\nEven for CoreCLR, it's good practice to allow core dumps at the OS level:\n\n```bash\nulimit -c unlimited\n```\n\nAnd if using **systemd**, add to your service unit:\n\n```ini\n[Service]\nLimitCORE=infinity\nEnvironment=DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1\nEnvironment=DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4\nEnvironment=DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName=/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\n```\n\n---\n\n## Quick Reference\n\n| | CoreCLR | NativeAOT |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Detection** | `libcoreclr.so` in `/proc/PID/maps` | No `libcoreclr.so` |\n| **Dump mechanism** | `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` env vars | Kernel `core_pattern` |\n| **Analysis tool** | `dotnet-dump analyze` | `gdb` / `lldb` |\n\nRun the detection command on your actual PID and I can help you apply the exact config.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"22196c48-21a8-4935-98bc-982dffbe7044","outputTokens":736,"requestId":"7654:2D596F:E56586:10D63FF:69FE93B8"},"id":"3e96d940-1d6e-4981-811f-da03a52688bf","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:54:16.694Z","parentId":"92f81af8-dba2-46e1-b128-c7e5549e7a8b"}
